{"id":65508,"date":"2022-10-18T15:27:30","date_gmt":"2022-10-18T20:27:30","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/?p=65508"},"modified":"2025-03-28T16:00:45","modified_gmt":"2025-03-28T21:00:45","slug":"how-to-combat-costs-with-google-ads-custom-segments","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/10\/18\/google-ads-custom-segments","title":{"rendered":"How to Combat Costs With Google Ads Custom Segments"},"content":{"rendered":"<p>When it comes to <span><a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/09\/21\/google-ads-audience-targeting-cheat-sheet\">Google Ads audience targeting<\/a>,<\/span> there are a number of different audiences you can use. They can be bucketed into three main types: Google\u2019s audience segments, &#8220;your data&#8221; segments, and &#8220;custom&#8221; segments.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/09\/google-ads-audience-targeting-cheat-sheet.png\" alt=\"google ads audience targeting cheat sheet\" width=\"720\" height=\"538\" class=\"size-full wp-image-64681 aligncenter\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/09\/google-ads-audience-targeting-cheat-sheet.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/09\/google-ads-audience-targeting-cheat-sheet-480x359.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Custom segments are what I want to dive into today, because in my opinion, they&#8217;re one of the most powerful and underutilized features in Google Ads. Read on to find out:<\/p>\n<ul>\n<li>What Google Ads custom segments are<\/li>\n<li>Why you should use them<\/li>\n<li>How to create custom segments in Google Ads<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2>What are custom segments in Google Ads?<\/h2>\n<p>Google Ads custom segments let you leverage Google\u2019s proprietary data about its users in ways that are unique to your business. You can create custom segments using up to three criteria:<\/p>\n<ol>\n<li>The interests and products\/services people are <strong>searching<\/strong> for<\/li>\n<li>The types of <strong>websites<\/strong> people browse<\/li>\n<li>The types of <strong>apps<\/strong> people use<\/li>\n<\/ol>\n<p>By &#8220;up to&#8221; three criteria, this means that you can target just one of those criteria or any combination of two or three.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/09\/google-ads-audience-targeting-custom-segments.png\" alt=\"google ads targeting - custom segment example\" width=\"720\" height=\"551\" class=\"size-full wp-image-64674 aligncenter\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/09\/google-ads-audience-targeting-custom-segments.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/09\/google-ads-audience-targeting-custom-segments-480x367.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>This custom segment targets all three criteria: interests, types of websites, and apps.<\/em><\/p>\n<p>Once you create a custom segment, you can add it to your Display, Discovery, or Video campaigns. You can also add custom segments to your audience signals for <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/07\/05\/performance-max-tips\">Performance Max campaigns<\/a>, which Google considers a best practice (and I agree).<\/p>\n<h2>Why you should use custom segments in Google Ads<\/h2>\n<p>There are two main reasons why I believe custom segments are so darn useful.<\/p>\n<h3>Highly specific targeting<\/h3>\n<p>First, while there are thousands of <span>Google Ads audience targeting<\/span> choices, many advertisers are just not able to find the right ones for them. For example, what if <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/05\/11\/target-audience\">your target audience<\/a> is digital marketing professionals? Or doctors? Or people who are alums of Ivy League universities?<\/p>\n<p>Custom segments let you create the perfect audience for your needs by leveraging Google\u2019s immense data about user behavior based on their searches, the websites they visit, and the apps they use.<\/p>\n<h3>Lower competition &amp; costs<\/h3>\n<p>Custom segments can <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/02\/21\/how-to-save-money-google-ads\">save you money on your Google Ads<\/a>. Since you\u2019re the only one who will have this custom segment in your account (after all, it is custom!), competition may be lower, which means potentially <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/why-google-ad-costs-are-rising-in-2025\">lower ad costs<\/a>.<\/p>\n<p>Also, we know that Search CPCs are rising, and Search ads are getting more and more expensive each year (<a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/online-advertising-benchmarks\">check our benchmarks!<\/a>) In comparison, CPCs on Discovery are generally quite affordable.<\/p>\n<p>Custom segments allow you to reach people who have been searching for your keywords, just not in the moment they\u2019re actually searching. Right people + different time = still powerful results. Create a Discovery campaign targeting a custom segment of your <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2014\/06\/30\/commercial-intent-keywords\">top Search keywords<\/a>, and watch some magic happen!<\/p>\n<div class='et-box et-shadow'>\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class='et-box-content'><p>\ud83d\udcb0 <strong>Find opportunities to save money in Google Ads with the<\/strong> <strong><a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/google-adwords?cid=Web_Any_InContentTextLink_PPC_AWGrader_AWGrader\">Free Google Ads Grader<\/a><\/strong>.<\/p><\/div><\/div>\n<h2>How to create a Custom segment in Google Ads<\/h2>\n<p>To create custom segments in Google Ads, go to Tools &amp; Settings, and then select Audience Manager.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/google-ads-custom-segments-tools-settings.png\" alt=\"google ads custom segments - audience manager\" width=\"720\" height=\"315\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-65513\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/google-ads-custom-segments-tools-settings.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/google-ads-custom-segments-tools-settings-480x210.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>Choose the Custom segments tab:<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/google-ads-custom-segments-creation.png\" alt=\"google ads custom segments tab\" width=\"720\" height=\"329\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-65514\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/google-ads-custom-segments-creation.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/google-ads-custom-segments-creation-480x219.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p>You can then create a custom segment using one or any combination of these three criteria:<\/p>\n<h3>1. Interests or behaviors<\/h3>\n<p>You can create a custom segment to target people with specific interests or purchase intentions, or who have searched specific terms on Google.<\/p>\n<p>For example, I\u2019ve run a YouTube campaign advertising my <span><a href=\"https:\/\/learn.jyll.ca\/courses\/insidegoogleads\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Google Ads course<\/a><\/span> targeted to a Custom segment of people who have searched for \u201cgoogle ads course,\u201d \u201cadwords course,\u201d \u201clearn google ads,\u201d \u201cgoogle ads training,\u201d etc.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/google-ads-custom-segment-search-terms.png\" alt=\"google ads custom segment creation from search terms\" width=\"720\" height=\"558\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-65516\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/google-ads-custom-segment-search-terms.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/google-ads-custom-segment-search-terms-480x372.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<p><strong>Note! <\/strong>There\u2019s one finicky little nuance to be aware of, though. If your custom segment includes a list of terms that people are searching for, this will only work as intended on Google-owned properties: Discovery and YouTube.<\/p>\n<p>On the Display network and Video partner sites, your search terms will be treated as general \u201cinterests\u201d rather than specific things people have searched for. So keep that in mind when <a href=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/blog\/ws\/2022\/10\/05\/types-of-google-ads\">picking your campaign type<\/a> and settings!<\/p>\n<h3>2. Types of websites<\/h3>\n<p>You can also create a custom segment based on the types of websites people browse.<\/p>\n<p>For example, a business I was advising was trying to reach dentists and people who work in dental offices, so they targeted a custom segment of industry news-type websites for dentists.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/google-ads-custom-segments-sites.png\" alt=\"google ads custom segments based on websites\" width=\"720\" height=\"553\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-65519\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/google-ads-custom-segments-sites.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/google-ads-custom-segments-sites-480x369.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<h3>3. Types of apps<\/h3>\n<p>And finally, you can create a Custom segment based on the types of apps people use.<\/p>\n<p>For example, if you want to reach small business owners using Google Ads, you can target a custom segment of people who have apps like Shopify, Wix, Etsy Seller, Ecwid Ecommerce, etc.<\/p>\n<p><img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/google-ads-custom-segment-apps.png\" alt=\"google ads custom segment creation from apps\" width=\"720\" height=\"554\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-65517\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/google-ads-custom-segment-apps.png 720w, https:\/\/www.wordstream.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/10\/google-ads-custom-segment-apps-480x369.png 480w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 0px) and (max-width: 480px) 480px, (min-width: 481px) 720px, 100vw\" \/><\/p>\n<h2>Start using Google Ads custom segments<\/h2>\n<p>Now can you see why I think Google Ads custom segments are underutilized? They&#8217;re a powerful way to target your prospects, reduce competition, and lower your costs. Use these tips and steps to start using them and getting more out of your budget!<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Learn how to wield the power of this underused Google Ads feature.<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":249,"featured_media":65528,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"open","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":{"_acf_changed":false,"_et_pb_use_builder":"","_et_pb_old_content":"","_et_gb_content_width":"","om_disable_all_campaigns":false,"footnotes":""},"categories":[101],"tags":[],"dipi_cpt_category":[],"class_list":["post-65508","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-google-ads"],"acf":[],"yoast_head":"<!-- This site is optimized with the Yoast SEO plugin v25.8 - https:\/\/yoast.com\/wordpress\/plugins\/seo\/ -->\n<title>Google